metadata.name: Störungen #218
metadata.description:
Störungen is an exercise in suprematism in generative art. Not a new concept by any means, but (hopefully) uniquely applied.

In this work a single line is drawn from the center of the artwork, spiraling out and being perturbed by various constraints and disturbed by various controlling forces. These perturbations produce different illusions and, when combined, create feeling.

This piece is created in p5js, but is also intended to be plotted. Plotting will not allow for the blurring or color in the piece, but will instead give you a single color version of the perturbed spiral that you can print.

Open the token in a new window and:
- add &highres=true to the URL to get a highres image for printing
- add &svg=true to have the program create a plottable SVG
- double-click to download a PNG or SVG

metadata.name: Ari's Thread #44
metadata.description:
I side with the idea that we made this reality so weird merely to satisfy our -psychotic- need to overcomplicate things. Not you, of course.

That's why I believe that our choices don't "create our own path" but a maze for others to (try to) solve.
This God or that One or none, the old songs or the new ones, rooting for or against…
The deepest we meet into each other's maze, the more choices we share. Reciprocally, when we lack the interest to explore even a couple of turns, we're but a first impression to each other.

This work examines those ideas by continually presenting options to N individuals and then tracking their choices, which in turn generates different outputs at different depths.

To access them:
- press "S" for story mode, the sequence of choices
  - then, press "1" through "5" to change the speed
- press "L" for landscape, the first impression
- press "D" to see the details and view the mazes (may take a while)

metadata.name: ARAUCO #9
metadata.description:
The Araucaria Araucana, also known as pewén, is a sacred tree for the Mapuche and an emblem of Chile. With an origin dating back 260 million years to the Triassic period, it is part of the oldest forests on the planet. These ancient trees are endangered due to logging, forest fires, and grazing.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the Wünelfe star, and the staggered cross Ngümin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest. 

–

Press 's' to export a 4960x7016 PNG file suitable for A2 printing at 300 dpi.

Made with p5js.

Patricio Isaías, September 2022

metadata.name: Symbology437 #17
metadata.description:
Abstract, distorted compositions using symbols from the original IBM VGA codepage 437 character set. The symbols were created in code as bitmaps, scaled, and then drawn onto the canvas. The shading is based on the characters and sets from ANSI and ASCII art styles. 

There are 4 main types of outputs:
- Abstracts, 50%
- Random characters, 25%
- One of 16 preset character layouts, 25%
- One of 16 custom symbol PFP styles that will be 10% of the total outputs

For abstracts, there are several main styles created from layering different base shapes: circles, filled circles, rectangles, flow field lines, and rain-like streaks.

Color combinations include monochromatic, green or amber, dark mode, and multicolor.

Press 's' to save the image. The size is 2318x3000px, and for PFPs, the size is 3000x3000px.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #559
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Sound Therapy #43
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps rendering
Play the instrument by moving, clicking & dragging your cursor / finger

The combination of real-time graphics and generative music has always fascinated me, and what could be a better addition to the mix than a physics library for creating playful instruments. The instrument will play itself with a predefined pattern, but you can take over the controls and immerse yourself in the sound therapy. Enjoy and relax!

Keyboard
[ space ] - pause
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - pause
